                   "message":  "KEYCOMMAND-SAVE-RENAME: rename EditorKeyCommand::MarkSaved -\u003e Save\n\nThe Ctrl+S key command\u0027s name predated its behavior. SCENE-SAVE-WIRING\nrepointed the handle_key_command arm from a bare command_bus.mark_saved()\nbookmark to self.handle_save_request() — a real Save (write the live World to\nthe open .rge-scene / .rge-project on disk, then mark the bus saved point on\nsuccess). This renames the variant to match that behavior.\n\n- EditorKeyCommand::MarkSaved -\u003e Save (enum def, from_key_press, the\n  handle_key_command arm, the key-map doc table, and the variant doc comment,\n  which drops the now-satisfied \"rename to Save is a deferred follow-up\" note).\n- save_request.rs / lifecycle/tests.rs / keyboard_command_bus_round_trip.rs:\n  the doc links, the dispatch calls, and the from_key_press expected value.\n\nScope: editor-shell-internal variant only (grep confirms no consumer outside\neditor-shell). NOT renamed: EditorShell::mark_saved_command() and the bus op\ncommand_bus.mark_saved() — those are genuine mark-the-cursor-saved operations\nand keep their accurate names.\n\nPure identifier + prose rename: no behavior change, no serde (Debug-only\nderive), no Cargo.toml. 4 files. `rg \u0027MarkSaved\u0027 crates` is empty.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
